==English==
===Etymology===
Hebrew [[בבל]] ‘Babylon’, from Akkadian ''bāb ili'' ‘gate of God’; in [[Genesis]] associated with the idea of confusion.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'beɪbəl/

===Noun===
'''Babel'''

# The city and tower in the land of [[Shinar]] where the [[confusion]] of [[language]]s took place, according to the [[Bible]].
#:*Therefore is the name of it called '''Babel'''. - ''Gen. xi. 9.''
# ''Alternative spelling of'' [[babel]].

